body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/448\n\n## Problem (data loss class)\nA custom field registered `--type boolean` via `pm schema add-field` is silently never persisted when set through its auto-derived flag (`--customer-impact true` style): create/update succeeds, no warning, field absent from item and changed_fields. Boolean is one of four documented custom-field types; any boolean field (customer_impact, regression, is_blocker...) loses data on every write while reporting success.\n\n## Repro (from GH-448, pm 2026.7.4)\nfresh tracker -> `pm schema add-field customer_impact --type boolean --commands create,update` -> `pm create ... --customer-impact true` -> field missing.\n\n## Definition of done\nBoolean custom fields persist through create/update (coercion fixed); regression spec across all four field types; silent-drop path converted to hard error for unknown/uncoercible custom values; verified in sandbox from packed tarball."
